# Fiction
- [Reamde](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reamde) by [Neal Stephenson](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neal_Stephenson). Key element of novel is a fictional [MMORPG](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/MMORPG).  Topics covered include [goldfarming](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gold_farming).
- Bruce Sterling's [Maneki Neko](http://www.lightspeedmagazine.com/fiction/maneki-neko/) (short story) - What if the net knew what you liked... and what you hated? What if everyone were given small tasks (quests, even) that promoted good behavior and discouraged bad behavior?
- [Sight](http://vimeo.com/46304267) short film depicting a future world where augmented reality and gaming collide.

# Reads
* [Karen's List of Gamification Links](http://www.diigo.com/list/bowdenartist/gamification) You can subscribe via RSS to my list on Diigo to receive an update each time I add new items.
- [When Did Addiction Become A Good Thing?](http://gigaom.com/2012/09/02/when-did-addiction-become-a-good-thing/) Jason Hreha essay on GigaOM questioning "the ethics of manufacturing desire"
- Good overview of the gamification from the .net Magazine [The pro's guide to gamification](http://www.netmagazine.com/features/pro-s-guide-gamification)
- Gamification blog by Kevin Werbach & Dan Hunter [www.gamifyforthewin.com](http://gamifyforthewin.com)
-  Harnessing the Power of Feedback Loops By Thomas Goetz [www.wired.com](http://www.wired.com/magazine/2011/06/ff_feedbackloop/all/1)
- 20 Best Blogs About Game-Based Learning - [An Overview](http://blogs.msdn.com/b/ukfe/archive/2012/08/20/the-20-best-blogs-about-game-based-learning.aspx) by Tim Bush
-  Using gamification in a smart city - [Urban360](http://urban360.me/2012/08/24/if-urban-life-is-a-game-smart-cities-are-the-playgrounds-gamification-civic-rewards-and-crowd-sourcing-strategies-for-connected-and-savvy-cities/)
- [Games for Change Part 1](http://www.bottomlineperformance.com/games-for-change-part-1-the-power-of-urgent-optimism-in-learning-games/) from Bottom-Line Performance by Steve Boller.
- [Center4Edupunx](http://center4edupunx.org/) Bootstrapping Our Way Across the Curriculum blog.
- [MOOCology](http://learnos.wordpress.com/2012/08/22/moocology/) by Viplav Baxi.
- [Designing Games with a Purpose](http://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?doid=1378704.1378719) An academic paper on the subject. 
- [Enterprise Gamification The Next Big Paradigm](http://www.infosysblogs.com/bpm-eai/2012/02/enterprise_gamification_-_the.html) A short article around the oppurtunities for Service Providers. 
- [Reverse Gamification and the future of everything](http://nanodome.wordpress.com/2011/09/06/reverse-gamification-and-the-future-of-everything/) Some thoughts on 'forward' and 'reverse' gamification. 
- [Instant Gratification and Education: Strange Bedfellows?](http://www.onlineuniversities.com/blog/2011/12/instant-gratification-and-education-strange-bedfellows/) An article about gamification and education. 
- [The Gamification of Education Infographic](http://www.knewton.com/gamification-education/) Infographic about gamification and education. 
- [Learning in Tandem: The Shamification of Gamification](http://learningintandem.blogspot.ca/2012/05/shamification-of-gamification.html) "We shouldn’t be shaming people for embracing the concept of gamification; we should be educating people on what good game and gamification design looks like so that they can spot the bad design."
- Why not gamify your workplace? (http://www.gamificationofwork.com)
- [Why Games Don't Teach](http://www.astd.org/Publications/Blogs/L-and-D-Blog/2012/04/Why-Games-Dont-Teach) Match game features to learning outcomes.
- [Can't Play Won't Play](http://www.hideandseek.net/2010/10/06/cant-play-wont-play/) interesting piece from Margaret Robertson on whether gamification is the right term: she defines pointsification as a subset.
- [Pintrest site on Gamification](http://pinterest.com/bubbleequity/gamification/) a collection of articles on the subject on a Pintrest board.
- Karl Kapp's article (June 2012) [Games, Gamification, and the Quest for Learner Engagement](http://www.astd.org/Publications/Magazines/TD/TD-Archive/2012/06/Games-Gamification-and-the-Quest-for-Learner-Engagement)
-Ashlee Vance Galactic Crack Bloomburg Businessweek http://www.businessweek.com/articles/2013-04-18/multiplayer-game-eve-online-cultivates-a-most-devoted-following CCP Games, Eve Online and  a staff economist to manage the game's economy
- [What is a Game? by Wolfgang Kramer](http://www.thegamesjournal.com/articles/WhatIsaGame.shtml)
- [How ‘Gamification’ Can Make Your Customer Service Worse](http://www.wired.com/wiredenterprise/2012/11/gamification-customer-service/)
- [How wearable tech may keep you alive a little longer](http://www.backbonemag.com/Magazine/2013-11/archive/how-wearable-tech-may-keep-you-alive.aspx)
- [Utilities Will Spend $65 Million on Gamified Applications in 2016 to Engage Consumers, According to IDC Energy Insights ](http://www.idc.com/getdoc.jsp?containerId=prUS24598214)
- [How to make a good Puzzle Game](http://www.rockpapershotgun.com/2015/01/22/how-to-make-a-puzzle-game/)

